<br>
********<br>
things like better abilities and spells, are also given, but class unique.<br>
a level 55 mage, should not have a better pet than a level 61 mage. theres no other way to say it. <br>
********<br>
<br>
I have to disagree here.  Your logic here says that by the same token, (s)he shouldn't have better than a 56th level mage either.  <br>
<br>
This is incorrect.  The 55th put in the work, and got the epic.  The 61st without the epic did not.  There is no &quot;given benefit.&quot;  There is only &quot;Earned&quot; benefit.  Your hypothetical 61st did not feel it worthwhile to pursue the epic pet - knowing full well what that pet could do.  <br>
<br>
The quests for these new pets are gimp quests.  Kill enough stuff, score some pages, turn them in and POOF!  New pet.  <br>
<br>
If that 61st level Magician wants a big-ass wonkin elemental, (s)he better get his/her butt down to SK and start looking for flappy horses.<br>
<br>
Very likely, if things continue to L200 as you suggest, there will be &quot;staged epics&quot;, so that an individual can either pursue standard pets - the Ford models - and have a passable elemental, or (s)he can time out from levelling/raiding to go acquire a Porsche.<br>
<br>
I busted my ass early on for this (might very well be the lowest-level magician on my server to have done so), and I can tell you straight up it's tougher for a lower-level mage to get this thing done.  I would think the 46th level magician SHOULD have a better pet than a 60th for doing this quest.  (S)He won't nuke hardly as well, but certainly will have a kick-ass pet.  <br>
<br>
Those folks who didn't pursue the epic early, instead got levels or aa's.  That means they differentiated themselves down a different path.  You're arguing here for a homogeneous bunch of interchangeable people.  Blah.  I was psyched to be a 54th magician that everyone wanted in their group because my pet could massacre whatever critter we were dealing with.<br>
<br>
Eventually, &quot;standard&quot; pets will eclipse the epic.  Not this time.  Probably when the effort to acquire the standard pet is greater than the effort to acquire the epic.  i.e., a while from now.<br>
<br>
********<br>
Quote:<br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
There should be other ways to work for rewards, like questing, tradeskills, raiding.. that reward the player in a comparable magnitude as xping.<br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
<br>
as an avid quester and tradeskiller, i completely agree with this statement. the rewards from questing/tradeskilling/raiding should be of proportionally comparable magnitude as that you would receive from leveling. key phrase being proportionally comparable magnitude.<br>
********<br>
<br>
Those tradeskillers and questers DO get rewards appropriate to their actions.  They get cash and trophy items for tradeskilling, and they get quest rewards for questing.  <br>
<br>
You're again asking for a free ride here.  <br>
<br>
If folks want the dang pet, do the dang quest.  All this whining sounds like &quot;but I don't WANT to have to do all that work.&quot;  <br>
<br>
Tough beans.  Get off your duffs, recruit some friends, and go do the dang quest.  You want the best pet?  Earn the freaking thing.  At 61st, we're not talking about a monumental effort.  Otherwise, learn to cope with the normal pet for your level.  <br>
<br>
I wouldn't expect to see a pet equalling the epic until at least L70 - and in fact, it probably won't be as good in the conglomerate sense.  Maybe the earth will have the hps and will hit as hard...maybe air will have the proc and the stun...maybe the fire will have the bigass fireshield...<br>
<br>
I understand you probably get tired of using the same pet over and over again, or maybe you don't want to be tied to summoning the orb, etc.  I can see why you'd feel that way.  I just don't agree that some L61 should be able to go farm a page or three and convert it into Uber_Pet_01.  <br>
<br>
If they want to bump off Gonad, they're going to have to do some severe work for it.<br>
<br>
  Big D<br>
<br>
<br>
Edit:<br>
<br>
Tain wrote:<br>
**********<br>
&quot;Please don't belittle my acomplishment because I'm not a &quot;high Enough&quot; level mage&quot;<br>
<br>
We do not mean to belittle you or your accomplisments. But, do you feel it is fair for a 52 mage to have a pet that is as good as a 65 mage? Do any 52 wizards have the same (best) nuke as a 65? Or any other class in that regard? <br>
**********<br>
<br>
Tain, you are totally disregarding that the 65th level mage has nukage and other spells that will flatten the 52nd.  The 52nd has NO chance to compete in the same arena.  Yes, the 52 SHOULD have a better pet, because that 52nd worked his ass to the bone to get it - and the 65th DID NOT.  That 65th has every opportunity to pursue the epic, and chooses not to.  Don't pretend that he's some poor, oppressed, can't-afford-a-cup-of-coffee bum.  At 65th, he could probably sell a chunk of gear and make the 300k he'd need to buy all the pieces for MQ.  <br>
<br>
This is not rocket science, folks.  We are not our pets alone.  A 65th without epic is not a lesser being than a 52nd with it.  Quite the contrary.  <br>
