Heroes</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=duftin>Duftin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#333333>(10/24/02 4:53:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=784.topic&index=77>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: missing the point about pets</span><hr size=1> I have lurked on this board for a long time now, but I don't post that often, mainly because I am only a lowly (compared to the more vocal and more experienced mages on this board) level 37 mage.  I don't know a lot about the endgame, just what I've read on this board.  I can totally understand both points of view on this subject...The epic'ed mages don't want to see their time and effort eclipsed by something that doesn't take anywhere near the investment of time, blood, sweat, and (I dare say in many cases) tears.  I can also understand why people wouldn't want the mage class to be limited to the power of the epic, which was introduced during the Kunark era, and wil soon be vastly underpowered in the 61-65 game, as it exists now.<br>
<br>
How do we handle this problem?  Obviously no-one has come up with an equitable solution, judging by the vociferous, and often vemonous, responses to this thread.  It's sad to see the mage population at such odds over what should occur to keep both sides happy.  I would like to offer a suggestion to help ease the dispute that doesn't look like it will ever end.  This solution incorporates several suggestions already in this thread, so I don't want the credit for this, I just want to offer an opinion that might help settle the masses.<br>
<br>
Anyway, here it is...<br>
<br>
There are two distinct groups of mages that exist nowadays: the epic'ed mage, and the non-epic'ed mage.  I suggest that the epic staff (as suggested in several other posts) become a focus item for the new pets from 61-65.  I also suggest that the pets from 61-65 be ***in their specific areas (melee, casting, tanking, etc.)*** stronger than the epic pet.  That would make the epic pet still the best overall pet, but in certain situations the new pets might be better.  HOWEVER, with the epic staff, the new pets would be focused, and therefore stronger than the pets that could be cast by a non-epic'ed mage.  And, to cap out this solution, at level 65, not below, you would have access to a quest to get epic v2.0.  Sections of this quest may be able to be completed at a lower level, BUT they would have to be done at level 65 in order for them to &quot;count&quot; in the completion of the quest.  This could be accomplished by using the new &quot;flags&quot; concept unveiled for PoP.  This epic v2.0, as an integral part of the quest, would include turning in an epic staff.  The new epic would also be a pet, but stronger than any of those that precede it, in a way that obviously makes it superior, but not completely unbalancing to the game itself (just as epic v1.0 was, in its time).<br>
<br>
What are the upsides to this solution?<br>
1.  Those mages that hold epic v1.0 still have an advantage over those that don't, because they will receive better pets from 61-65, and have an easier time completing epic v2.0.<br>
2.  Those mages that don't hold epic v1.0 have access to great pets as well, but they will never be able to equal the power of those pets of mages with epic v1.0.<br>
3.  It creates a scenario that allows epic'ed mages to still hold a distinct advantage over those mages without the original epic, both during levels 61-65, and when it comes to completion of epic quest v2.0.  In essence, to become one of the truly elite mages, one has to go through both quests.<br>
<br>
I fully realize that this plan is not perfect, so please, poke holes in it, rip it apart, do as you will.  I just wanted to voice my opinion on this hot topic, and hope to get some constructive discussion going.  It has been proven (especially with this expansion) that if we have reasonable requests to better the class, and keep it balanced with others, and within our own ranks, there is a chance that SOE, VI, whoever is in charge will listen.<br>
<br>
Ok, I'm finished...Flame away.<br>
<br>
Duftin Fizzlefoot<br>
Mage of the 37th season, Luclin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xantherssb>XantherSSB</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 80<br> <font color=#333333>(10/24/02 5:57:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=784.topic&index=78>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: missing the point about pets</span><hr size=1> I hope that verant indeed does add Epic 2.0 for all classes.  As hard as our epic was to get, wasnt that shaky thrilled feeling you got when you sat down to mem that Orb spell, in the shadow of the Master, a great thing?<br>
