You still didn't address my argument: The fact that other classes almost certainly will get better pets than our epic, without having done a quest that compares to our epic.<br>
****<br>
<br>
That's correct - I didn't.  I haven't seen any other class' pet in comparison to ours yet, so I'm not in a position to claim that we're disadvantaged or not.  <br>
<br>
****<br>
If you get what you're asking for (out of pure pride and spite for those that did not do the quest it seems) then magicians lose ground to other classes. This is the point that I was trying to make.<br>
****<br>
<br>
First of all, never read motive into what I say, unless I specifically denote why I'm saying something.<br>
<br>
****<br>
Other classes will get pet upgrades in the same manner we do in PoP. Just because their new pets are better than our epic, do you think VI will make them do a quest harder than the epic to obtain them? NO. <br>
<br>
Mages, however, should have to do both the epic and an even harder quest to get better pets than epic.. hmm, how balanced is that?<br>
****<br>
<br>
As has been mentioned before, levelling is easy.  It is a byproduct of spending time playing.  <br>
<br>
Other classes may indeed get better pets - and I do expect we'll exceed them in some form or fashion.  Probably most if not all forms or fashions.  How that is done is up to VI.  <br>
<br>
I simply find it &quot;sickening&quot; to hear people whine about how so-and-so pet &quot;should be better&quot; than the epic simply because it's 61st level.  61st.  So what?  Why does this make any difference over 60th?  Or 59th?  58th?  49th?  That is what I find &quot;childish and selfish&quot; - that's a &quot;gimme&quot; attitude that I hear in those voices.  Whether I'm correct or not in hearing that, it's still the impression I get.  <br>
<br>
BFD.  So we have new pets.  Maybe they're better, maybe they're worse than the epic.  I actually prefer Balanz' idea of having them exceed the epic in one form or another, but not in all respects, leaving it to be the best general-purpose pet in the bag.<br>
<br>
Sounds, actually, like that's exactly what is happening - and it sounds like our utility spells are designed so that we can actually *build* pets that are better in many ways than the epic.  This works just dandy for me - since these utility spells can also be used on the epic itself.  <br>
<br>
